# Regression test for the cross-thread ISR dispatch bug: confirms the timer1
# COMPA ISR actually fires and its Serial/digitalWrite/millis side effects
# work from the background timer thread. OCR1A=100 with prescaler 8 fires
# roughly every 32.7ms, so the first fire is safely within 200ms -- exact
# pin13 state isn't asserted since it flips on every fire and is sensitive to
# real-time scheduling jitter relative to the loop's own 200ms print cadence.
0.15, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "ISR fired, count=1"
0.25, ASSERT, SERIAL_CONTAINS, "loop: digitalRead(13)="
